  <bead id="ddx-1865eadc">
    <title>agent: record retry and review decision audit fields</title>
    <description>
PROBLEM&#xA;The worker result JSON and event payloads do not yet carry enough typed audit data to explain why a bead closed, retried, escalated, reconciled, or went to operator attention. That makes the Niflheim-style failure families hard to classify after the fact and leaves empty review results looking like success.&#xA;&#xA;ROOT CAUSE&#xA;`cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go:154-174` defines `ExecutionCycleTrace`, but its current fields are still sparse and optional, so the result can omit the classification trail the worker used. `cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_review.go:168-193` also allows a zero-value `ReviewResult` with no verdict, evidence, or skip reason, which makes the review part of the audit trail ambiguous unless additional gating is added elsewhere.&#xA;&#xA;PROPOSED FIX&#xA;- Extend result serialization and event bodies with `failure_class`, `retry_action`, `escalation_count`, requested/actual routing facts, review status/verdict or explicit skip reason, and land/reconcile status.&#xA;- Ensure the Niflheim scenario families all emit those fields so a reader can tell whether the worker closed, retried, escalated, reconciled, or parked the bead.&#xA;- Keep the audit fields stable and machine-readable so regression tests can assert on them directly.&#xA;&#xA;NON-SCOPE&#xA;- Do not redesign the retry policy in this child.&#xA;- Do not duplicate the land/review gating logic covered by sibling children; this child only makes the decision visible.
    </description>
    <acceptance>
1. `TestExecuteBeadResult_NiflheimEvidence_CycleTraceCarriesDecisionAudit` proves result JSON/event bodies include `failure_class`, `retry_action`, `escalation_count`, requested/actual routing facts, review status/verdict or explicit skip reason, and land/reconcile status for the Niflheim scenario families.&#xA;2. The audit data is present for the empty-review, land-failure, decomposed-parent, and pre-claim-warning scenarios that appear in this bead.&#xA;3. `cd cli &amp;&amp; go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -run &#39;CycleTraceCarriesDecisionAudit&#39; -count=1` passes.&#xA;4. `cd cli &amp;&amp; go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... -count=1` passes.&#xA;5. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.
    </acceptance>
