.ddx/attachments/ddx-dc2249e9/events.jsonl:9:{"actor":"ddx","body":"Bead ddx-dc2249e9 — no_changes rationale\n\nWhat is done\n============\nThe acceptance criterion is already satisfied at the base revision\n(d01bc4453e9913335945ea1461485b5c0516a5bb).\n\n  cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/executions.spec.ts:362-406\n\ncontains the test:\n\n  test('execution detail renders cost tier information', async ({ page }) => { ... })\n\nIt loads the execution detail page (/nodes/.../executions/<id>), routes the\nNodeInfo / Projects / ExecutionDetail GraphQL operations, asserts the heading\nmatches the execution id, and asserts the Cost quick-fact cell is present and\nrenders \"$0.0400\" — the value fmtCost(0.04) produces from blockExec.costUsd.\n\nThe Cost quick-fact cell is rendered unconditionally by the detail page at\ncli/.../executions/[executionId]/+page.svelte:188-189 via fmtCost (defined at\n:127-130 as `$${c.toFixed(4)}`), so the assertion is grounded in the actual UI.\n\nThis test was added in commit 472d4aaf\n(\"test(e2e): verify cost tier info renders in execution detail [ddx-dc2249e9]\")\nand merged into main via 4bab0a16. It is present on the current base revision.\n\nWhy no new commit\n=================\nThe prior REVIEW:BLOCK note (\"Diff contains only an execution result.json\nartifact; no test file changes are present\") referred to the most recent\nattempt (20260501T035858), which produced only an evidence artifact because\nthe test had already landed in 472d4aaf. The bead was re-queued, but the AC is\nalready met on main — there is no further test code to add or change in this\nworktree without duplicating the existing test.\n\nAdding a duplicate or trivially-renamed test would be churn, not progress.\nThe existing test fully covers the acceptance criterion: it lives in\nexecutions.spec.ts, verifies cost-tier information is rendered in the\nexecution detail view, and is wired into the same Playwright suite that runs\nin CI.\n\nWhat a follow-up would need\n