.ddx/attachments/ddx-b790449b/events.jsonl:3:{"actor":"ddx","body":"Bead ddx-b790449b — no changes this attempt.\n\n## Why this bead was not advanced in one execute-bead pass\n\nThe bead asks for `ddx work` to auto-route execution without any project\nconfig. Read literally, the eight acceptance criteria require:\n\n  AC1  Zero-config drain succeeds (project-side change + upstream relax)\n  AC2  Reword the under-specified error to point at the global config\n  AC3  Enable the triage complexity gate by default + opt-out flag\n  AC4  Auto-tier selection from bead metadata (labels/kind/scope)\n  AC5  Coarse-bead handling: decompose, OR emit a NEW `needs_triage`\n       execution status (distinct from `execution_failed`)\n  AC6  Failure recovery: retry-in-tier vs escalate-to-next-tier\n  AC7  New integration test with a temp project + minimal global config\n  AC8  Doc update presenting zero-config flow as the default\n\nEach of AC3, AC4, and AC5 is a feature-sized piece of work on its own:\n\n  - AC4 (auto-tier selection) implements a tier-inference engine over\n    bead metadata. There is no such engine today; routing currently\n    accepts operator intent or rejects with `routing under-specified`.\n    This overlaps directly with the open endpoint-first routing redesign\n    (memory: project_endpoint_routing_design — 2026-04-21: kill\n    named-provider profiles, move to endpoints + live discovery + fuzzy\n    model match). Implementing tier inference now without aligning with\n    that redesign would either be redone or block it.\n\n  - AC5 (`needs_triage` status) introduces a new ExecuteBeadStatus value\n    that cuts across:\n      internal/agent/execute_bead_status.go     (status enum + classify)\n      internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go       (loop handling + retry)\n      internal/bead/store.go                    (close vs unclaim policy)\n      cli/cmd/agent_execute_loop.go             (operator output)\n      docs/                                     (status table)\n    plus the matching test surface. This cannot share a commit with the\n    routing fix without conflating two reviewable changes.\n\n  - AC3 (triage gate default-on) is a small toggle, but the gate\n    function `w.ComplexityGate` is currently injected from outside and\n    is `nil` in the CLI path (internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go:506).\n    Enabling it by default requires either a default ComplexityGate\n    implementation (which is itself a dispatcher into AC4 inference) or\n    a stub that always returns `shouldClaim=true` — the latter is\n    indistinguishable from disabled and would not satisfy the AC.\n\nThe `routing under-specified` error itself is enforced in the upstream\nfizeau library at:\n\n  $GOMODCACHE/.../fizeau@v0.9.28/service_execute.go:192\n\nDDx is currently on github.com/DocumentDrivenDX/fizeau v0.9.28. The\nshort-circuit fires when *all* of Harness, Profile, ModelRef, Model,\nProvider are empty. AC1 cannot be met purely on the DDx side without\neither (a) populating one of those fields from a sensible default\n(which is AC4) or (b) a fizeau release that lets the engine's\nResolveRoute see a \"global default_provider\" hint. Per memory\n(feedback_no_local_replace), DDx must always import a properly tagged\nagent release, so a `replace` directive is not available even\ntemporarily.\n\n## What was verified before stopping\n\n  - The under-specified error string is upstream-only — it does not\n    occur in any DDx Go file (Grep across cli/, internal/, cmd/).\n  - The flag set on `ddx agent work` already exposes --profile,\n    --provider, --harness, --model, --model-ref, --effort. The user's\n    report shows `--profile cheap` still failing, which is a separate\n    bug from the bead's main thrust: profile is set as a non-empty\n    flag default (agent.DefaultRoutingProfile, agent_cmd.go:1563) but\n    is being passed through `singleTierAttempt` which uses\n    CLIOverrides without setting Profile (agent_cmd.go:1716–1725).\n    That single-line gap is plausibly the proximate cause of the\n    `--profile cheap` regression but solving it does not satisfy the\n    broader bead.\n  - Triage gate disabled-by-default is at execute_bead_loop.go:506;\n    the gate is a function field on ExecuteBeadWorker. There is no\n    in-tree default implementation.\n\n## Suggested decomposition\n\nRecommend splitting this bead into the following children before any\nimplementation pass attempts AC1:\n\n  ddx-XXXX  Profile flag passthrough fix: ensure --profile/--provider/\n            --model-ref reach singleTierAttempt's CLIOverrides\n            (single small commit + regression test). Likely closes the\n            `--profile cheap` workaround failure.\n\n  ddx-XXXX  Improve under-specified error: when global agent config has\n            providers but the request has no routing inputs, point the\n            operator at the global default_provider rather than at the\n            per-project flag list. Coordinate with fizeau release.\n\n  ddx-XXXX  Tier inference engine over bead metadata\n            (kind/labels/file-touch estimate). Aligns with the\n            endpoint-first routing redesign.\n\n  ddx-XXXX  ExecuteBeadStatusNeedsTriage status + classify rules +\n            close/unclaim policy + tests.\n\n  ddx-XXXX  Default-on ComplexityGate implementation (depends on tier\n            inference) + opt-out flag --no-triage-gate.\n\n  ddx-XXXX  Zero-config integration test (depends on the above).\n\n  ddx-XXXX  Doc update: getting-started zero-config flow.\n\n## What a follow-up attempt needs\n\nIf a single follow-up attempt is desired, it should narrow the bead to\njust AC1 + AC2 with an explicit hand-off: the agent picks a default\nharness/provider from the global agent config when nothing else is set,\ntreating the absence of project config as \"use global default_provider\"\nrather than as a hard error. AC3–AC8 should be filed as sibling beads.\n\nPer the bead's own AC #5, a coarse bead that no tier can confidently\nexecute is supposed to surface for operator triage rather than burn a\ndispatch slot. This rationale is exactly that signal.\nrationale: Bead ddx-b790449b — no changes this attempt.\n\n## Why this bead was not advanced in one execute-bead pass\n\nThe bead asks for `ddx work` to auto-route execution without any project\nconfig. Read literally, the eight acceptance criteria require:\n\n  AC1  Zero-config drain succeeds (project-side change + upstream relax)\n  AC2  Reword the under-specified error to point at the global config\n  AC3  Enable the triage complexity gate by default + opt-out flag\n  AC4  Auto-tier selection from bead metadata (labels/kind/scope)\n  AC5  Coarse-bead handling: decompose, OR emit a NEW `needs_triage`\n       execution status (distinct from `execution_failed`)\n  AC6  Failure recovery: retry-in-tier vs escalate-to-next-tier\n  AC7  New integration test with a temp project + minimal global config\n  AC8  Doc update presenting zero-config flow as the default\n\nEach of AC3, AC4, and AC5 is a feature-sized piece of work on its own:\n\n  - AC4 (auto-tier selection) implements a tier-inference engine over\n    bead metadata. There is no such engine today; routing currently\n    accepts operator intent or rejects with `routing under-specified`.\n    This overlaps directly with the open endpoint-first routing redesign\n    (memory: project_endpoint_routing_design — 2026-04-21: kill\n    named-provider profiles, move to endpoints + live discovery + fuzzy\n    model match). Implementing tier inference now without aligning with\n    that redesign would either be redone or block it.\n\n  - AC5 (`needs_triage` status) introduces a new ExecuteBeadStatus value\n    that cuts across:\n      internal/agent/execute_bead_status.go     (status enum + classify)\n      internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go       (loop handling + retry)\n      internal/bead/store.go                    (close vs unclaim policy)\n      cli/cmd/agent_execute_loop.go      