led as sibling beads.\n\nPer the bead's own AC #5, a coarse bead that no tier can confidently\nexecute is supposed to surface for operator triage rather than burn a\ndispatch slot. This rationale is exactly that signal.\nresult_rev=68f5c39d11bb6e4e7e9a9327691d9baf3420b3cc\nbase_rev=68f5c39d11bb6e4e7e9a9327691d9baf3420b3cc","created_at":"2026-05-01T20:53:16.329540344Z","kind":"execute-bead","source":"ddx agent work","summary":"already_satisfied"}
.ddx/attachments/ddx-b790449b/events.jsonl:11:{"actor":"erik","body":"Bead ddx-b790449b — no new changes this attempt; implementation already\nlanded in pre-execute checkpoint e2f720e8.\n\n## State of the AC at start of this attempt\n\nThe pre-execute-bead checkpoint commit e2f720e8 already contains the\nfollowing implementation work (added between the prior attempt's\nno_changes return and this attempt's spawn):\n\n  AC1 — Zero-config drain succeeds\n        cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go: zero-config auto-route block at L1613–L1623\n        (defaults profile to \"cheap\" when no routing flags + no project\n        config). Verified by TestZeroConfigWork_NoConfigDoesNotEmitUnderSpecified\n        in cli/cmd/zero_config_work_test.go (passes, count=1).\n\n  AC2 — Friendly error when global config also empty\n        cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go: pre-flight at L1625–L1634 returns\n        \"no providers configured: add at least one provider to\n        ~/.config/agent/config.yaml ...\" instead of letting fizeau emit\n        \"routing under-specified\". Verified by\n        TestZeroConfigWork_NoGlobalProvidersFriendlyError (passes).\n\n  AC3 — Triage gate warning suppressed by default\n        cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go: L501–L510 — the\n        \"warning: triage complexity gate is disabled\" line is gone when\n        ComplexityGate == nil. Test updated:\n        TestComplexityGateNilNoWarning (cli/internal/agent/triage_test.go)\n        asserts the legacy warning does not appear (passes).\n\n  AC5 — Coarse-bead handling\n        cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go: Step 0 size-check section\n        prepended to both executeBeadInstructionsClaudeText and\n        executeBeadInstructionsAgentText (L1210–L1228 and L1274–L1292).\n        Decomposition responsibility now lives in the LLM prompt: the\n        agent is instructed to file child beads via `ddx bead create`,\n        wire deps via `ddx bead dep add`, annotate the parent, and\n        write a no_changes_rationale.txt — exactly the path this very\n        attempt is taking.\n\n  AC7 — Integration test\n        cli/cmd/zero_config_work_test.go covers the AC's scenario\n        (temp project + .ddx/beads.jsonl, minimal global config,\n        `ddx work --local --once`, asserts no \"routing under-specified\"\n        and no .ddx/config.yaml side-effect file).\n\n  AC8 — Documentation update\n        website/content/docs/getting-started.md gained a \"Drain the\n        Queue (Zero-Config)\" section presenting the no-flags flow as\n        the default, with project-level routing as an advanced\n        override.\n\n## What is NOT in checkpoint e2f720e8\n\n  AC4 — Per-bead auto-tier selection from bead metadata\n        Currently the auto-route picks one profile (\"cheap\") for the\n        whole loop run. Per-bead tier inference from labels/kind/scope\n        is unimplemented. Doing it well requires plumbing per-bead\n        routing decisions through the work singleTierAttempt\n        path and adding a small classifier (label-based heuristics +\n        catalog tier lookup). This overlaps with the open\n        endpoint-first routing redesign (project memory\n        project_endpoint_routing_design, 2026-04-21) — ad-hoc tier\n        inference now will be redone or block that redesign.\n\n  AC6 — Explicit retry-vs-escalate policy verification\n        Existing tier escalation in execute_bead_loop.go does run\n        (winning_tier=exhausted events confirm it once dispatched),\n        but the AC asks for an explicit policy doc + test that\n        transient failures retry within tier and substantive failures\n        escalate. No new test was added to lock that contract in.\n\n## Why this attempt makes no new commits\n\nTwo reasons:\n\n1. The work that satisfies AC1, AC2, AC3, AC5, AC7, AC8 is already\n   on the project branch via checkpoint commit e2f720e8. Re-applying\n   it as my own commit is impossible (already committed) and adding a\n   cosmetic completion-marker commit just for bead bookkeeping is\n   noise the reviewer cannot meaningfully approve.\n\n2. The remaining gaps (AC4, AC6) are each feature-sized and are\n   best filed as child beads per the Step 0 instructions the prior\n   pass installed. Per memory feedback_no_local_replace and project\n   project_endpoint_routing_design, AC4 in particular should not\n   land as a bolt-on ahead of the endpoint-first redesign.\n\n## Recommended next action\n\nClose ddx-b790449b as substantially-complete and file two child\nbeads:\n\n  - ddx-XXXX  Per-bead auto-tier selection from bead metadata\n              (depends on / aligned with endpoint-first routing\n              redesign). Adds label/kind heuristics + catalog tier\n              lookup wired into singleTierAttempt.\n\n  - ddx-XXXX  Lock retry-vs-escalate contract: a regression test\n              asserting transient (network/rate-limit/timeout)\n              failures retry within tier while substantive\n              (probe_ok+exec_fail) failures escalate.\n\nVerification commands run before stopping:\n\n  go build ./...                                                 # green\n  go test -run TestZeroConfigWork -count=1 ./cmd                 # PASS\n  go test -run TestComplexityGate  -count=1 ./internal/agent     # PASS\nrationale: Bead ddx-b790449b — no new changes this attempt; implementation already\nlanded in pre-execute checkpoint e2f720e8.\n\n## State of the AC at start of this attempt\n\nThe pre-execute-bead checkpoint commit e2f720e8 already contains the\nfollowing implementation work (added between the prior attempt's\nno_changes return and this attempt's spawn):\n\n  AC1 — Zero-config drain succeeds\n        cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go: zero-config auto-route block at L1613–L1623\n        (defaults profile to \"cheap\" when no routing flags + no project\n        config). Verified by TestZeroConfigWork_NoConfigDoesNotEmitUnderSpecified\n        in cli/cmd/zero_config_work_test.go (passes, count=1).\n\n  AC2 — Friendly error when global config also empty\n        cli/cmd/agent_cmd.go: pre-flight at L1625–L1634 returns\n        \"no providers configured: add at least one provider to\n        ~/.config/agent/config.yaml ...\" instead of letting fizeau emit\n        \"routing under-specified\". Verified by\n        TestZeroConfigWork_NoGlobalProvidersFriendlyError (passes).\n\n  AC3 — Triage gate warning suppressed by default\n        cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_loop.go: L501–L510 — the\n        \"warning: triage complexity gate is disabled\" line is gone when\n        ComplexityGate == nil. Test updated:\n        TestComplexityGateNilNoWarning (cli/internal/agent/triage_test.go)\n        asserts the legacy warning does not appear (passes).\n\n  AC5 — Coarse-bead handling\n        cli/internal/agent/execute_bead.go: Step 0 size-check section\n        prepended to both executeBeadInstructionsClaudeText and\n        executeBeadInstructionsAgentText (L1210–L1228 and L1274–L1292).\n        Decomposition responsibility now lives in the LLM prompt: the\n        agent is instructed to file child beads via `ddx bead create`,\n        wire deps via `ddx bead dep add`, annotate the parent, and\n        write a no_changes_rationale.txt — exactly the path this very\n        attempt is taking.\n\n  AC7 — Integration test\n        cli/cmd/zero_config_work_test.go covers the AC's scenario\n        (temp project + .ddx/beads.jsonl, minimal global config,\n        `ddx work --local --once`, asserts no \"routing under-specified\"\n        and no .ddx/config.yaml side-effect file).\n\n  AC8 — Documentation update\n        website/content/docs/getting-started.md gained a \"Drain the\n        Queue (Zero-Config)\" section presenting the no-flags flow as\n        the default, with project-level routing as an advanced\n        override.\n\n## What is NOT in checkpoint e2f720e8\n\n  AC4 — Per-bead auto-tier selection from bead metadata\n        Currently the auto-route picks one profile (\"cheap\") for the\n 